owners would not suffer barm, even if the sailors said that they acted in accordance with instructions.” See how even with this liberality of mine in making defense the sailors can scarcely be harmed—and the owners not even as much as that. But indeed, since the sailors simply defended themselves and that defense was on every count justified, what conclusion can we reach except that the Tuscana should make good to us ⁸⁸ as people who have been despoiled, everything that has been taken away and the losses incurred, the expense, the interest, the profits, and so forth, to the last penny?
